      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPUNKYS GOTSECRETS (4) has been competitive of late and kept the ball rolling last time when he led and stuck on to finish 6 metres from the winner in fourth at Menangle. Had placed in his previous three outings at this circuit and distance. Could break through. AVENGER NZ (3) gave a good sight last start when he led and boxed on for third, beaten 3.4 metres at this venue. Should be prominent again from this draw and with his A-game he is good enough to win a race of this calibre. HES MY REASON (5) came from the back row to miss by a head last start and looks suited back to the mile having scored back-to-back wins over the distance here earlier in the campaign. GENERAL ROCKER (1) led from wider to score by 2.2 metres at Tamworth last start. Has the speed to take advantage of the ace draw so could take the next step.",
